  %li
    Should I use lab PC to access my e-mail?
    %ul
      %li No.
      %li
        %hr/
  %li
    Should I use lab PC to submit a credit card number?
    %ul
      %li No.
      %li
        %hr/
  %li
    Should I use lab PC to access my amazon account?
    %ul
      %li No.
      %li
        %hr/
  %li
    How can I safely connect to Amazon and e-mail from lab?
    %ul
      %li Bring your laptop or phone (which uses encrypted connections).
      %li
        %hr/
  %li
    Which parts of AWS interest us the most?
    %ul
      %li EC2
      %li S3
      %li
        %hr/
  %li
    How would you introduce EC2 to a new person?
    %ul
      %li I would show how to setup an instance.
      %li I would show how to ask EC2 for a PEM file.
      %li I would show how to ssh to an existing instance with the PEM file.
      %li
        %hr/

  %li
    What is a PEM file?
    %ul
      %li A PEM file replaces the need for a password.
      %li
        %hr/

  %li
    How do I get a PEM file?
    %ul
      %li I download a PEM file from EC2 web-UI.
      %li
        %hr/

  %li
    Once I have a PEM file where to store it?
    %ul
      %li I give it a simple name like aws1.pem
      %li I put it in this folder: ~/.ssh/
      %li
        %hr/
  %li
    Once I have a PEM file how to use it?
    %ul
      %li
        I use it like this:
        %pre
          %code ssh -i ~/.ssh/aws1.pem ubuntu@someip
      %li
        %hr/
  %li
    Is it possible to deploy a copy www.spy611.com to EC2?
    %ul
      %li Yes.
      %li Directions:
      %li
        %a(href='http://www.spy611.com/software/spy611aws' target='x')
          http://www.spy611.com/software/spy611aws
      %li
        %hr/
  
  %li
    What is S3?
    %ul
      %li S3 is an Amazon service I use to store and serve large files.
      %li
        %hr/
  %li
    How to get started with S3?
    %ul
      %li Use the web-UI to create a bucket with a unique name.
      %li Use the web-UI to upload files into the bucket.
      %li Use the web-UI to make the files public or private.
      %li
        Use the shell to interact with S3:
        %a(href='http://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/using-s3-commands.html' target='x')
          http://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/using-s3-commands.html
      %li
        %hr/
  %li
    Why use S3?
    %ul
      %li It's cheap.
      %li It's popular.
      %li It's useful.
      %li Most Data Scientists will encounter S3; that is where the data is.
      %li
        %hr/

  %li
    Can I use a PEM file to access S3?
    %ul
      %li Probably not.
      %li
        %hr/

  %li
    Linux vs Mac vs Windows, what is the data scientist opinion?
    %ul
      %li It depends on the use-case.
      %li If you need to use Excel, Windows is a good choice.
      %li If you can affort it, Mac is best.
      %li Linux offers the best software installation experience.
      %li To build then host a Data Science App, Linux is best.
      %li
        %hr/
  %li
    How to get started with Linux?
    %ul
      %li Linux inside VirtualBox on Mac.
      %li Linux on EC2.
      %li Linux on Chromebook via crouton.
      %li Linux installed on laptop.
      %li Linux on laptop from Zareason.com
      %li Last choice: Linux inside VirtualBox on windows.
      %li
        %hr/

  %li
    Which flavor of Linux should I learn first?
    %ul
      %li Ubuntu 14.04 or Ubuntu 16.04
      %li
        %hr/
  %li
    How is AWS Linux different than Laptop Linux?
    %ul
      %li No access to GUI tools.
      %li Variable cost (by the hour).
      %li Access to internet is excellent.
      %li Easy to setup.
      %li Easy to backup.
      %li Easy to duplicate.
      %li Easy to scale.
      %li
        %hr/
  %li
    How to get help with Linux?
    %ul
      %li
        Site:
        %a(href='http://askubuntu.com' target='x')
          http://askubuntu.com
      %li
        %hr/
  
  %li
    What is Git?
    %ul
      %li Git is software to store and share groups of files.
  %li
    Why use git?
    %ul
      %li I use git store and share groups of files.
      %li I use git to 'time-travel' when I work with software.
      %li I use git to see differences between similar software.
      %li I use git to deploy software to heroku and EC2.
      %li I use git to present syntax to students.
      %li
        %hr/
  %li
    What are the top git use-cases?
    %ul
      %li Clone a repo: git clone
      %li Add a file to a repo: git add, git commit
      %li Check status of repo: git status
      %li Initialize a repo: git init
      %li Pull your changes into my repo: git pull
      %li Push my changes into other repo: git push
      %li
        %hr/
  %li
    What is Heroku?
    %ul
      %li Heroku allows me to serve my websites for free.
      %li I use git to copy website from laptop into Heroku.
      %li
        %hr/
  %li
    Why use Heroku?
    %ul
      %li Heroku is low cost (usually free).
      %li Heroku is simple.
      %li Heroku performs well.
      %li
        %hr/
  
